I stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of careless driving. I acknowledge that my actions on the day in question were reckless and could have had dire consequences. I was driving aggressively, exceeding the speed limit, and even thoughtlessly responded to a text message while behind the wheel. This resulted in a collision with a guardrail, fortunately without causing harm to anyone else.

Looking back, I now fully comprehend the severity of my actions and the potential risks I posed not only to myself but to others on the road. I deeply regret my behavior and the dangerous situation I created. It is clear that my actions were irresponsible and inexcusable.

While this incident is indeed a stain on my otherwise clean record, I am pleading guilty with full acceptance of responsibility. At 37 years old, I understand the gravity of this offense. Furthermore, I would like to emphasize that I have made regular donations to the British Heart Foundation, demonstrating my commitment to contributing positively to society.

Your Honor, I request that you take into consideration my guilty plea as a mitigating factor. I am remorseful for my actions and I assure you that I have learned from this experience. I am committed to taking the necessary steps to prevent such behavior from happening again in the future. I have already enrolled in a defensive driving course to improve my skills and road awareness.

I acknowledge that my previous penalty points for speeding indicate a lapse in judgment, but I am determined to make amends for my actions. I am willing to face the consequences and take any necessary steps to rectify the harm I have caused. I understand the seriousness of the offense and I am committed to providing compensation for any damages resulting from the accident.

In conclusion, I humbly implore the court to consider my guilty plea, regret, and commitment to change as factors in sentencing. I am truly remorseful for the dangerous situation I created and I assure you that I have learned and grown from this experience. I will do everything within my power to prevent such actions from happening again in the future.

Thank you for your attention to this matter.

Sincerely,

Charlotte Porter

