Your Honor,

I stand before you today to respectfully plead guilty to the offense of careless driving. I acknowledge the seriousness of my actions that day and the potential harm I could have caused to both myself and others on the road.

I recognize that my behavior on the day in question, driving aggressively and exceeding the speed limit, was reckless and unacceptable. Additionally, I made the irresponsible decision to answer a text message while operating a vehicle, further compromising my attention to the road. This led to the unfortunate collision with a guardrail, although thankfully no one else was harmed.

Reflecting upon this incident, I am deeply remorseful for my actions and the dangerous situation I created. I completely understand the gravity of my offense and take full responsibility for the consequences that ensued.

Thank you for your consideration, Your Honor.

Sincerely,

Charlotte Porter
